  "name": "Pace and space",
  "category": "Strategy & Concepts",
  "sub_category": "General Strategy",
  "description": "An offensive philosophy that emphasizes a fast tempo (pace) and spreading the floor with elite shooters (space). The goal is to maximize the number of possessions and take high-value shots (three-pointers or layups) early in the shot clock, often within the first 7 seconds. By positioning shooters beyond the arc, it clears the paint, making it extremely difficult for the defense to help on drives or pick-and-rolls without leaving a shooter open.",
